HEADWORD: Rinderpest
<hw>Rin"der*pest</hw> <pr>(r⟦icr⟧n"d⟦etil⟧r*p⟦ecr⟧st)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr. <ets>rind</ets>, pl. <ets>rinder</ets>,
cattle + <ets>pest</ets> pest, plague.]</ety> <def>A highly contagious
distemper or murrain, affecting neat cattle, and less commonly sheep and
goats; -- called also <altname>cattle plague</altname>, <altname>Russian
cattle plague</altname>, and <altname>steppe
murrain</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rindle</ent>⟦br⟧
